From 23bfbbd7bd793b7566558f3e688d681644ce47e7 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Harsh Kumar Bijlani <hbijlani@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Fri, 16 May 2025 15:18:03 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM: DP: wifi: ath12k: Validate peer id before searching
 for peer

HW may pass invalid peer id in error scenarios coming from Rx WBM release or
Rx monitor ring.

Avoid searching the peer for this invalid peer id, rather return NULL.

Signed-off-by: Harsh Kumar Bijlani <hbijlani@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/dp_peer.c | 3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/dp_peer.c b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/dp_peer.c
index ee583ce..34e8901 100644
--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/dp_peer.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/dp_peer.c
@@ -439,6 +439,9 @@ struct ath12k_dp_peer *ath12k_dp_peer_find_by_peerid_index(struct ath12k_dp *dp,
 	RCU_LOCKDEP_WARN(!rcu_read_lock_held(),
 			 "ath12k dp peer find by peerid index called without rcu lock");
 
+	if (peer_id >= ATH12K_PEER_ID_INVALID)
+		return NULL;
+
 	index = ath12k_dp_peer_get_peerid_index(dp, peer_id);
 
 	return rcu_dereference(dp_pdev->dp_hw->dp_peer_list[index]);
-- 
2.34.1

